.SH NAME
Alien::Build::Plugin::Fetch::NetFTP \- Plugin for fetching files using Net::FTP
.SH VERSION
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 2.84
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 5
\& use alienfile;
\& share {
\&   start_url \*(Aqftp://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/make\*(Aq;
\&   plugin \*(AqFetch::NetFTP\*(Aq;
\& };
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Note: in most case you will want to use Alien::Build::Plugin::Download::Negotiate
instead.  It picks the appropriate fetch plugin based on your platform and environment.
In some cases you may need to use this plugin directly instead.
.PP
This fetch plugin fetches files and directory listings via the \f(CW\*(C`ftp\*(C'\fR, protocol using
Net::FTP.
.SH PROPERTIES
.IX Header "PROPERTIES"
.SS url
.IX Subsection "url"
The initial URL to fetch.  This may be a directory or the final file.
.SS ssl
.IX Subsection "ssl"
This property is for compatibility with other fetch plugins, but is not used.
.SS passive
.IX Subsection "passive"
If set to true, try passive mode FIRST.  By default it will try an active mode, then
passive mode.
